"function_name": "get_cx_to_on_air_backlog", "node_type": "kpi", "node_id": "a3f0a09c-5a86-4bcd-8d8a-7842e73c5e3e", "node_label": "CX to On-Air Backlog", "description": "Counts projects that have completed construction but have not yet gone On-Air (current snapshot), and breaks the backlog down by the most actionable blocking stage.\\n\\nEntities / joins: Project (stg_ndpd_mbt_tmobile_macro_combined) grouped by rgn_region, m_area, m_market, pj_general_contractor; keyed by pj_project_id.\\n\\nInput columns:\\n- pj_project_id\\n- ms_1555_construction_complete_actual\\n- pj_completion_objective_actual_date\\n- pj_a_5270_integration_start_finish\\n- ms_1970_integration_complete_actual\\n- ms_1559_cop_approved_by_t_mobile_actual\\n- rgn_region, m_area, m_market, pj_general_contractor\\n\\nBacklog population definition:\\n- Backlog projects are those where:\\n  - ms_1555_construction_complete_actual IS NOT NULL\\n  - AND pj_completion_objective_actual_date IS NULL\\n\\nCore outputs (per grouping):\\n- backlog_count = COUNT(DISTINCT pj_project_id) over the backlog population\\n\\nBlocker-stage breakdown outputs (per grouping). Compute as counts over the backlog population using mutually exclusive stage logic, evaluated in this order:\\n1) backlog_integration_not_started_count:\\n   - pj_a_5270_integration_start_finish IS NULL\\n2) backlog_integration_in_progress_count:\\n   - pj_a_5270_integration_start_finish IS NOT NULL\\n   - AND ms_1970_integration_complete_actual IS NULL\\n3) backlog_post_integration_cop_pending_count:\\n   - ms_1970_integration_complete_actual IS NOT NULL\\n   - AND ms_1559_cop_approved_by_t_mobile_actual IS NULL\\n4) backlog_other_post_cop_count (optional catch-all to avoid silent leakage):\\n   - ms_1970_integration_complete_actual IS NOT NULL\\n   - AND ms_1559_cop_approved_by_t_mobile_actual IS NOT NULL\\n   - AND pj_completion_objective_actual_date IS NULL\\n\\nImplementation notes:\\n- Use COUNT(DISTINCT pj_project_id) for all counts.\\n- Ensure the breakdown stage counts sum to backlog_count when the optional catch-all is included.\\n- This is a CURRENT_DATE snapshot metric (no time bucketing).", "parameters": [], "output_columns": [{"name": "rgn_region", "type": "string", "nullable": false}, {"name": "m_area", "type": "string", "nullable": false}, {"name": "m_market", "type": "string", "nullable": false}, {"name": "pj_general_contractor", "type": "string", "nullable": false}, {"name": "backlog_count", "type": "number", "nullable": false}, {"name": "backlog_integration_not_started_count", "type": "number", "nullable": false}, {"name": "backlog_integration_in_progress_count", "type": "number", "nullable": false}, {"name": "backlog_post_integration_cop_pending_count", "type": "number", "nullable": false}, {"name": "backlog_other_post_cop_count", "type": "number", "nullable": false}, {"name": "breakdown_sums_to_backlog", "type": "boolean", "nullable": false}], "sample_output": [{"rgn_region": "CENTRAL", "m_area": "GREAT LAKES", "m_market": "CHICAGO", "pj_general_contractor": "impirium", "backlog_count": 1, "backlog_integration_not_started_count": 1, "backlog_integration_in_progress_count": 0, "backlog_post_integration_cop_pending_count": 0, "backlog_other_post_cop_count": 0, "breakdown_sums_to_backlog": true}, {"rgn_region": "CENTRAL", "m_area": "GREAT LAKES", "m_market": "CHICAGO", "pj_general_contractor": "meridian networks", "backlog_count": 1, "backlog_integration_not_started_count": 1, "backlog_integration_in_progress_count": 0, "backlog_post_integration_cop_pending_count": 0, "backlog_other_post_cop_count": 0, "breakdown_sums_to_backlog": true}, {"rgn_region": "CENTRAL", "m_area": "GREAT LAKES", "m_market": "CINCINNATI", "pj_general_contractor": "kcctech", "backlog_count": 1, "backlog_integration_not_started_count": 1, "backlog_integration_in_progress_count": 0, "backlog_post_integration_cop_pending_count": 0, "backlog_other_post_cop_count": 0, "breakdown_sums_to_backlog": true}], "row_count": 10}', nl_description: 'CX to On-Air Backlog = COUNT(DISTINCT pj_project_id) for projects where construction is complete (ms_1555_construction_complete_actual not null) and On-Air actual date is null (pj_completion_objective_actual_date null), grouped by rgn_region/m_area/m_market/pj_general_contractor, with each backlog project assigned to exactly one blocker stage based on integration start, integration completion, and COP approval milestone null-ness.', node_type: 'CORE', definition: 'CX to On-Air Backlog = COUNT(DISTINCT pj_project_id) for projects where construction is complete (ms_1555_construction_complete_actual not null) and On-Air actual date is null (pj_completion_objective_actual_date null), grouped by rgn_region/m_area/m_market/pj_general_contractor, with each backlog project assigned to exactly one blocker stage based on integration start, integration completion, and COP approval milestone null-ness.', kpi_python_function: 'def get_cx_to_on_air_backlog(execute_query, filters=None) -> list[dict]:\n    """Counts projects that are construction complete but not yet On-Air, grouped by region/area/market/GC,\n    with mutually-exclusive blocker-stage breakdown.\n\n    Backlog definition:\n      - ms_1555_construction_complete_actual IS NOT NULL\n      - AND pj_completion_objective_actual_date IS NULL\n\n    Stage assignment (in order):\n      1) integration_not_started: pj_a_5270_integration_start_finish IS NULL\n      2) integration_in_progress: pj_a_5270_integration_start_finish IS NOT NULL AND ms_1970_integration_complete_actual IS NULL\n      3) post_integration_cop_pending: ms_1970_integration_complete_actual IS NOT NULL AND ms_1559_cop_approved_by_t_mobile_actual IS NULL\n      4) other_post_cop (catch-all): ms_1970_integration_complete_actual IS NOT NULL AND ms_1559_cop_approved_by_t_mobile_actual IS NOT NULL AND pj_completion_objective_actual_date IS NULL\n    """\n\n    filters = filters or {}\n\n    # Accessor for Project does not expose the required milestone columns, so use raw SQL (single-table).\n    where_parts = []\n\n    # Optional dimension filters (only add if present). These column names are expected on the project table.\n    for k in ["rgn_region", "m_area", "m_market", "pj_general_contractor", "pj_project_id", "pj_project_status", "pj_project_type", "pj_program_name"]:\n        if k in filters and filters.get(k) is not None and str(filters.get(k)) != "":\n            v = str(filters.get(k)).replace("\'", "\'\'")\n            where_parts.append(f"{k} = \'{v}\'")\n\n    # Explicit snapshot metric: do not time-bucket. If caller passes start/end dates, ignore them (by design).\n\n    # Backlog population constraints\n    where_parts.append("ms_1555_construction_complete_actual IS NOT NULL")\n    where_parts.append("pj_completion_objective_actual_date IS NULL")\n\n    where_sql = ("WHERE " + " AND ".join(where_parts)) if where_parts else ""\n\n    sql = f"""\n        SELECT\n            rgn_region,\n            m_area,\n            m_market,\n            pj_general_contractor,\n            pj_project_id,\n            pj_a_5270_integration_start_finish,\n            ms_1970_integration_complete_actual,\n            ms_1559_cop_approved_by_t_mobile_actual,\n            pj_completion_objective_actual_date\n        FROM public.stg_ndpd_mbt_tmobile_macro_combined\n        {where_sql}\n    """.strip()\n\n    rows = execute_query(sql)\n\n    def norm_dim(val):\n        if val is None:\n            return "(null)"\n        s = str(val).strip()\n        return s if s != "" else "(blank)"\n\n    def is_nullish(v):\n        return v is None or str(v).strip() == ""\n\n    # Aggregate distinct pj_project_id per grouping and stage\n    agg = {}\n    for r in rows:\n        project_id = r.get("pj_project_id")\n        if is_nullish(project_id):\n            # Cannot COUNT(DISTINCT) without an identifier\n            continue\n\n        gk = (\n            norm_dim(r.get("rgn_region")),\n            norm_dim(r.get("m_area")),\n            norm_dim(r.get("m_market")),\n            norm_dim(r.get("pj_general_contractor"))\n        )\n        if gk not in agg:\n            agg[gk] = {\n                "backlog_projects": set(),\n                "integration_not_started": set(),\n                "integration_in_progress": set(),\n                "post_integration_cop_pending": set(),\n                "other_post_cop": set()\n            }\n\n        s = agg[gk]\n        s["backlog_projects"].add(project_id)\n\n        integ_start_finish = r.get("pj_a_5270_integration_start_finish")\n        integ_complete = r.get("ms_1970_integration_complete_actual")\n        cop_approved = r.get("ms_1559_cop_approved_by_t_mobile_actual")\n        onair_date = r.get("pj_completion_objective_actual_date")\n\n        # Mutually exclusive stage selection in the specified order\n        if is_nullish(integ_start_finish):\n            s["integration_not_started"].add(project_id)\n        elif (not is_nullish(integ_start_finish)) and is_nullish(integ_complete):\n            s["integration_in_progress"].add(project_id)\n        elif (not is_nullish(integ_complete)) and is_nullish(cop_approved):\n            s["post_integration_cop_pending"].add(project_id)\n        elif (not is_nullish(integ_complete)) and (not is_nullish(cop_approved)) and is_nullish(onair_date):\n            s["other_post_cop"].add(project_id)\n        else:\n            # If this happens, it indicates leakage vs the stated stage rules.\n            # We do not create an extra bucket; caller can detect via sums not matching backlog_count.\n            pass\n\n    out = []\n    for (rgn_region, m_area, m_market, pj_general_contractor), s in sorted(agg.items()):\n        backlog_count = len(s["backlog_projects"])\n        not_started = len(s["integration_not_started"])\n        in_progress = len(s["integration_in_progress"])\n        cop_pending = len(s["post_integration_cop_pending"])\n        other_post_cop = len(s["other_post_cop"])\n\n        out.append({\n            "rgn_region": rgn_region,\n            "m_area": m_area,\n            "m_market": m_market,\n            "pj_general_contractor": pj_general_contractor,\n            "backlog_count": backlog_count,\n            "backlog_integration_not_started_count": not_started,\n            "backlog_integration_in_progress_count": in_progress,\n            "backlog_post_integration_cop_pending_count": cop_pending,\n            "backlog_other_post_cop_count": other_post_cop,\n            "breakdown_sums_to_backlog": (not_started + in_progress + cop_pending + other_post_cop) == backlog_count\n        })\n\n    return out\n', kpi_source_columns: ['pj_project_id', 'ms_1555_construction_complete_actual', 'pj_completion_objective_actual_date', 'pj_a_5270_integration_start_finish', 'ms_1970_integration_complete_actual', 'ms_1559_cop_approved_by_t_mobile_actual', 'rgn_region', 'm_area', 'm_market', 'pj_general_contractor', 'pj_project_status', 'pj_project_type', 'pj_program_name'], session_id: '69a3d22f26e208edc083a06e', label: 'CX to On-Air Backlog', kpi_related_core_node_ids: ['project'], kpi_relationship_type: 'COMPUTES_FROM', kpi_kpi_id: 'a3f0a09c-5a86-4bcd-8d8a-7842e73c5e3e', entity_type: 'kpi', kpi_name: 'CX to On-Air Backlog', name: 'a3f0a09c-5a86-4bcd-8d8a-7842e73c5e3e', kpi_dimensions: ['rgn_region', 'm_area', 'm_market', 'pj_general_contractor'], kpi_description: 'Counts projects that have completed construction but have not yet gone On-Air in the current snapshot. The backlog is broken down by the most actionable blocking stage to identify where projects are getting stuck.', status: 'mentioned', node_id: 'a3f0a09c-5a86-4bcd-8d8a-7842e73c5e3e'});
