_milestone::date).\n5) Discard records where lead_days < 0.\n6) (Optional) Apply por_category filter; also (in the provided function) optional start_date/end_date filters applied to the segment end milestone date.\n7) Aggregate to one row per (rgn_region, m_area, m_market, pj_general_contractor, segment_name) and compute: avg_days, p50_days, p90_days, project_count = count distinct pj_project_id.', kpi_filters: '[{"name": "por_category", "type": "string", "description": "Filters projects to a specific POR category (e.g., por_category = \'Site Mod\')."}, {"name": "start_date", "type": "date", "description": "Optional date window lower bound applied to the segment end milestone date (end_dt must be on/after start_date)."}, {"name": "end_date", "type": "date", "description": "Optional date window upper bound applied to the segment end milestone date (end_dt must be on/before end_date)."}, {"name": "rgn_region", "type": "string", "description": "Optional filter by region."}, {"name": "m_area", "type": "string", "description": "Optional filter by area."}, {"name": "m_market", "type": "string", "description": "Optional filter by market."}, {"name": "pj_general_contractor", "type": "string", "description": "Optional filter by general contractor."}, {"name": "pj_project_id", "type": "string", "description": "Optional filter to one project."}]', kpi_contract: '{"function_name": "get_intermediate_ms_lead_time", "node_type": "kpi", "node_id": "e0d0a6af-286c-45db-ad7f-e8a08c4b138b", "node_label": "Intermediate MS Lead Time", "description": "Measures intermediate milestone-to-milestone calendar-day lead times across a fixed set of lifecycle segments, aggregated by portfolio dimensions. Source: stg_ndpd_mbt_tmobile_macro_combined. For each pj_project_id, compute lead_days = (end_milestone::date - start_milestone::date) for each segment; exclude records where start or end is NULL and exclude negative lead_days. Unpivot segments using UNION ALL into rows with: pj_project_id, rgn_region, m_area, m_market, pj_general_contractor, segment_name, start_milestone_name, end_milestone_name, lead_days. Segments: (1) Pre-NTP to Scoping Ready: ms_1310_pre_construction_package_received_actual \\u2192 ms_1323_ready_for_scoping_actual; (2) Scoping to NTP Approved: ms_1323_ready_for_scoping_actual \\u2192 ms_1507_tower_ntp_approved_actual; (3) NTP to Material Pickup: ms_1507_tower_ntp_approved_actual \\u2192 \\"pj_a_3925_msi_pickup_date_finish\\" (must be double-quoted); (4) Material to CX Start: \\"pj_a_3925_msi_pickup_date_finish\\" \\u2192 ms_1550_construction_start_actual; (5) CX Start to CX Complete: ms_1550_construction_start_actual \\u2192 ms_1555_construction_complete_actual; (6) CX Complete to IX Start: ms_1555_construction_complete_actual \\u2192 pj_a_5270_integration_start_finish; (7) IX Start to IX Complete: pj_a_5270_integration_start_finish \\u2192 ms_1970_integration_complete_actual; (8) IX Complete to COP: ms_1970_integration_complete_actual \\u2192 ms_1559_cop_approved_by_t_mobile_actual; (9) COP to On-Air: ms_1559_cop_approved_by_t_mobile_actual \\u2192 pj_completion_objective_actual_date. Aggregate output: one row per (rgn_region, m_area, m_market, pj_general_contractor, segment_name) with avg_days = AVG(lead_days), p50_days = percentile_cont(0.5) WITHIN GROUP (ORDER BY lead_days), p90_days = percentile_cont(0.9) WITHIN GROUP (ORDER BY lead_days), project_count = COUNT(DISTINCT pj_project_id). por_category is supported as an optional WHERE filter (e.g., por_category=\'Site Mod\') but is not part of the default GROUP BY.", "parameters": [{"name": "start_date", "type": "date", "description": "Filter by start date", "required": false, "sample_values": []}, {"name": "end_date", "type": "date", "description": "Filter by end date", "required": false, "sample_values": []}], "output_columns": [{"name": "rgn_region", "type": "string", "nullable": false}, {"name": "m_area", "type": "string", "nullable": false}, {"name": "m_market", "type": "string", "nullable": false}, {"name": "pj_general_contractor", "type": "string", "nullable": false}, {"name": "segment_name", "type": "string", "nullable": false}, {"name": "avg_days", "type": "number", "nullable": false}, {"name": "p50_days", "type": "number", "nullable": false}, {"name": "p90_days", "type": "number", "nullable": false}, {"name": "project_count", "type": "number", "nullable": false}], "sample_output": [{"rgn_region": "CENTRAL", "m_area": "GREAT LAKES", "m_market": "CHICAGO", "pj_general_contractor": "impirium", "segment_name": "CX Start to CX Complete", "avg_days": 16.0, "p50_days": 16.0, "p90_days": 16.0, "project_count": 1}, {"rgn_region": "CENTRAL", "m_area": "GREAT LAKES", "m_market": "DETROIT", "pj_general_contractor": "telcom construction", "segment_name": "NTP to Material Pickup", "avg_days": 154.0, "p50_days": 154.0, "p90_days": 154.0, "project_count": 1}, {"rgn_region": "CENTRAL", "m_area": "GREAT LAKES", "m_market": "MILWAUKEE", "pj_general_contractor": "kcctech", "segment_name": "Scoping to NTP Approved", "avg_days": 14.0, "p50_days": 14.0, "p90_days": 14.0, "project_count": 1}], "row_count": 10}', nl_description: 'Intermediate MS Lead Time = for each project and each fixed segment, calendar lead_days = (end_milestone_date - start_milestone_date) with NULL/negative durations excluded, then aggregated by (rgn_region, m_area, m_market, pj_general_contractor, segment_name) to compute AVG(lead_days), p50 and p90 (percentile_cont), and COUNT(DISTINCT pj_project_id).', node_type: 'CORE', definition: 'Intermediate MS Lead Time = for each project and each fixed segment, calendar lead_days = (end_milestone_date - start_milestone_date) with NULL/negative durations excluded, then aggregated by (rgn_region, m_area, m_market, pj_general_contractor, segment_name) to compute AVG(lead_days), p50 and p90 (percentile_cont), and COUNT(DISTINCT pj_project_id).', kpi_python_function: 'def get_intermediate_ms_lead_time(execute_query, filters=None) -> list[dict]:\n    import datetime\n\n    def _parse_date(val):\n        if val is None:\n            return None\n        if isinstance(val, datetime.date) and not isinstance(val, datetime.datetime):\n            return val\n        if isinstance(val, datetime.datetime):\n            return val.date()\n        s = str(val).strip()\n        if not s or s.lower() in ("null", "none", "nan"):\n            return None\n        # Handle \'YYYY-MM-DD\' and timestamps like \'YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS[.ffffff][+TZ]\'\n        try:\n            # datetime.fromisoformat handles many ISO-like forms\n            return datetime.datetime.fromisoformat(s.replace("Z", "+00:00")).date()\n        except Exception:\n            pass\n        for fmt in ("%Y-%m-%d", "%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S", "%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S.%f"):\n            try:\n                return datetime.datetime.strptime(s[:26], fmt).date()\n            except Exception:\n                continue\n        return None\n\n    # Optional filters supported by KPI request\n    filters = filters or {}\n\n    # If a date window is provided, we apply it to the *end milestone* date (per-segment)\n    # in Python (since milestone columns are wide and segment-specific).\n    start_date = _parse_date(filters.get("start_date"))\n    end_date = _parse_date(filters.get("end_date"))\n\n    # Build a lightweight SQL to pull only needed columns from the wide table.\n    # Tier-1 accessors don\'t expose the milestone date columns required, so we use raw SQL.\n    where_parts = []\n    # Allow filtering by portfolio dimensions and por_category (explicitly requested)\n    for k in ("rgn_region", "m_area", "m_market", "pj_general_contractor", "pj_project_id", "por_category"):\n        if k in filters and filters.get(k) is not None and str(filters.get(k)).strip() != "":\n            v = str(filters.get(k)).replace("\'", "\'\'")\n            where_parts.append(f"{k} = \'{v}\'")\n\n    where_sql = ("WHERE " + " AND ".join(where_parts)) if where_parts else ""\n\n    sql = f"""\n        SELECT\n            pj_project_id,\n            rgn_region,\n            m_area,\n            m_market,\n            pj_general_contractor,\n            por_category,\n            ms_1310_pre_construction_package_received_actual,\n            ms_1323_ready_for_scoping_actual,\n            ms_1507_tower_ntp_approved_actual,\n            \\"pj_a_3925_msI_pickup_date_finish\\",\n            ms_1550_construction_start_actual,\n            ms_1555_construction_complete_actual,\n            pj_a_5270_integration_start_finish,\n            ms_1970_integration_complete_actual,\n            ms_1559_cop_approved_by_t_mobile_actual,\n            pj_completion_objective_actual_date\n        FROM public.stg_ndpd_mbt_tmobile_macro_combined\n        {where_sql}\n    """\n\n    rows = execute_query(sql)\n\n    segments = [\n        {\n            "segment_name": "Pre-NTP to Scoping Ready",\n            "start_col": "ms_1310_pre_construction_package_received_actual",\n            "end_col": "ms_1323_ready_for_scoping_actual",\n            "start_name": "ms_1310_pre_construction_package_received_actual",\n            "end_name": "ms_1323_ready_for_scoping_actual",\n        },\n        {\n            "segment_name": "Scoping to NTP Approved",\n            "start_col": "ms_1323_ready_for_scoping_actual",\n            "end_col": "ms_1507_tower_ntp_approved_actual",\n            "start_name": "ms_1323_ready_for_scoping_actual",\n            "end_name": "ms_1507_tower_ntp_approved_actual",\n        },\n        {\n            "segment_name": "NTP to Material Pickup",\n            "start_col": "ms_1507_tower_ntp_approved_actual",\n            "end_col": "pj_a_3925_msI_pickup_date_finish",\n            "start_name": "ms_1507_tower_ntp_approved_actual",\n            "end_name": "pj_a_3925_msI_pickup_date_finish",\n        },\n        {\n            "segment_name": "Material to CX Start",\n            "start_col": "pj_a_3925_msI_pickup_date_finish",\n            "end_col": "ms_1550_construction_start_actual",\n            "start_name": "pj_a_3925_msI_pickup_date_finish",\n            "end_name": "ms_1550_construction_start_actual",\n        },\n        {\n            "segment_name": "CX Start to CX Complete",\n            "start_col": "ms_1550_construction_start_actual",\n            "end_col": "ms_1555_construction_complete_actual",\n            "start_name": "ms_1550_construction_start_actual",\n            "end_name": "ms_1555_construction_complete_actual",\n        },\n        {\n            "segment_name": "CX Complete to IX Start",\n            "start_col": "ms_1555_construction_complete_actual",\n            "end_col": "pj_a_5270_integration_start_finish",\n            "start_name": "ms_1555_construction_complete_actual",\n            "end_name": "pj_a_5270_integration_start_finish",\n        },\n        {\n            "segment_name": "IX Start to IX Complete",\n            "start_col": "pj_a_5270_integration_start_finish",\n            "end_col": "ms_1970_integration_complete_actual",\n            "start_name": "pj_a_5270_integration_start_finish",\n            "end_name": "ms_1970_integration_complete_actual",\n        },\n        {\n            "segment_name": "IX Complete to COP",\n            "start_col": "ms_1970_integration_complete_actual",\n            "end_col": "ms_1559_cop_approved_by_t_mobile_actual",\n            "start_name": "ms_1970_integration_complete_actual",\n            "end_name": "ms_1559_cop_approved_by_t_mobile_actual",\n        },\n        {\n            "segment_name": "COP to On-Air",\n            "start_col": "ms_1559_cop_approved_by_t_mobile_actual",\n            "end_col": "pj_completion_objective_actual_date",\n            "start_name": "ms_1559_cop_approved_by_t_mobile_actual",\n            "end_name": "pj_completion_objective_actual_date",\n        },\n    ]\n\n    # Build unpivoted lead-time facts in Python\n    facts = []\n    for r in rows:\n        pj_project_id = r.get("pj_project_id")\n        dims = {\n            "rgn_region": r.get("rgn_region"),\n            "m_area": r.get("m_area"),\n            "m_market": r.get("m_market"),\n            "pj_general_contractor": r.get("pj_general_contractor"),\n        }\n\n        for seg in segments:\n            start_dt = _parse_date(r.get(seg["start_col"]))\n            end_dt = _parse_date(r.get(seg["end_col"]))\n            if start_dt is None or end_dt is None:\n                continue\n            lead_days = (end_dt - start_dt).days\n            if lead_days is None or lead_days < 0:\n                continue\n            # Apply optional date range filter to the end milestone date\n            if start_date and end_dt < start_date:\n                continue\n            if end_date and end_dt > end_date:\n                continue\n\n            facts.append({\n                "pj_project_id": pj_project_id,\n                **dims,\n                "segment_name": seg["segment_name"],\n                "start_milestone_name": seg["start_name"],\n                "end_milestone_name": seg["end_name"],\n                "lead_days": lead_days,\n            })\n\n    # Aggregate: one row per (rgn_region, m_area, m_market, pj_general_contractor, segment_name)\n    def _percentile_cont(sorted_vals, p):\n        n = len(sorted_vals)\n        if n == 0:\n            return None\n        if n == 1:\n            return float(sorted_vals[0])\n        # Continuous percentile like PostgreSQL percentile_cont\n        pos = p * (n - 1)\n        lo = int(pos)\n        hi = min(lo + 1, n - 1)\n        frac = pos - lo\n        return float(sorted_vals[lo] + (sorted_vals[hi] - sorted_vals[lo]) * frac)\n\n    groups = {}\n    for f in facts:\n        key = (\n            f.get("rgn_region"),\n            f.get("m_area"),\n            f.get("m_market"),\n            f.get("pj_general_contractor"),\n            f.get("segment_name"),\n        )\n        g = groups.setdefault(key, {"vals": [], "projects": set()})\n        g["vals"].append(f["lead_days"])\n        if f.get("pj_project_id") is not None:\n            g["projects"].add(f["pj_project_id"])\n\n    out = []\n    for key, g in groups.items():\n        rgn_region, m_area, m_market, pj_general_contractor, segment_name = key\n        vals = sorted(g["vals"])\n        avg_days = (sum(vals) / len(vals)) if vals else None\n        out.append({\n            "rgn_region": rgn_region,\n            "m_area": m_area,\n            "m_market": m_market,\n            "pj_general_contractor": pj_general_contractor,\n            "segment_name": segment_name,\n            "avg_days": float(avg_days) if avg_days is not None else None,\n            "p50_days": _percentile_cont(vals, 0.5),\n            "p90_days": _percentile_cont(vals, 0.9),\n            "project_count": len(g["projects"]),\n        })\n\n    return out\n', kpi_source_columns: ['pj_project_id', 'rgn_region', 'm_area', 'm_market', 'pj_general_contractor', 'por_category', 'ms_1310_pre_construction_package_received_actual', 'ms_1323_ready_for_scoping_actual', 'ms_1507_tower_ntp_approved_actual', 'pj_a_3925_msi_pickup_date_finish', 'ms_1550_construction_start_actual', 'ms_1555_construction_complete_actual', 'pj_a_5270_integration_start_finish', 'ms_1970_integration_complete_actual', 'ms_1559_cop_approved_by_t_mobile_actual', 'pj_completion_objective_actual_date'], session_id: '69a3d22f26e208edc083a06e', label: 'Intermediate MS Lead Time', kpi_related_core_node_ids: ['project'], kpi_relationship_type: 'COMPUTES_FROM', kpi_kpi_id: 'e0d0a6af-286c-45db-ad7f-e8a08c4b138b', entity_type: 'kpi', kpi_name: 'Intermediate MS Lead Time', name: 'e0d0a6af-286c-45db-ad7f-e8a08c4b138b', kpi_dimensions: ['rgn_region', 'm_area', 'm_market', 'pj_general_contractor', 'segment_name'], kpi_description: 'Measures calendar-day lead times between predefined intermediate lifecycle milestones for projects. It helps evaluate how long projects spend in each segment of the delivery lifecycle when viewed across portfolio breakdowns.', status: 'mentioned', node_id: 'e0d0a6af-286c-45db-ad7f-e8a08c4b138b'});
CREATE (:BKGNode {kpi_source_tables: ['public.stg_ndpd_mbt_tmobile_macro_combined'], nl_business_rule: '', kpi_formula_description: 'gap = run_rate − backlog, where run_rate = COUNT(DISTINCT projects completed in trailing 12 weeks) / 12 and backlog = COUNT(DISTINCT projects that meet readiness gates and are not started as of CURRENT_DATE).', kpi_output_schema: '[{"column": "rgn_region", "type": "string", "description": "Region."}, {"column": "m_area", "type": "string", "description": "Area."}, {"column": "m_market", "type": "string", "description": "Market."}, {"column": "pj_general_contractor", "type": "string", "description": "General contractor."}, {"column": "run_rate", "type": "float", "description": "Average weekly distinct completed projects over the trailing 12 weeks (completed_12w / 12)."}, {"column": "backlog", "type": "int", "description": "Count of distinct projects that meet readiness gates and have not started as of CURRENT_DATE."}, {"column": "gap", "type": "float", "description": "Capacity vs demand gap (run_rate minus backlog)."}]', kpi_business_logic: '1) For each (rgn_region, m_area, m_market, pj_general_contractor), count distinct pj_project_id with construction complete actual date in [CURRENT_DATE-84 days, CURRENT_DATE+1 day) => completed_12w.\n2) Compute run_rate = completed_12w / 12; if no completed projects, use 0.\n3) For the same grouping, count distinct pj_project_id where construction start actual is NULL and readiness gates are satisfied => backlog; if none, use 0.\n4) Compute gap = run_rate - backlog.\n5) Return one row per distinct (rgn_region, m_area, m_market, pj_general_contractor) present in the base data (with non-null m_market and pj_general_contractor).', kpi_filters: '[{"name": "rgn_region", "type": "string", "description": "Limits results to a specific region."}, {"name": "m_area", "type": "string", "description": "Limits results to a specific area."}, {"name": "m_market", "type": "string", "description": "Limits results to a specific market."}, {"name": "pj_general_contractor", "type": "string", "description": "Limits results to a specific general contractor."}, {"name": "pj_program_name", "type": "string", "description": "Limits results to a specific program name."}, {"name": "pj_project_type", "type": "string", "description": "Limits results to a specific project type."}]', kpi_contract: '{"function_name": "get_capacity_vs_demand_gap", "node_type": "kpi", "node_id": "ea9583cb-1701-45ef-a2db-5cc07b01948c", "node_label": "Capacity vs Demand Gap", "description": "Computes the current execution gap per (Market, General Contractor) as: (Weekly GC Run Rate) \\u2212 (Ready Site Backlog), anchored to CURRENT_DATE. Interpreting sign: positive => implied spare capacity/underutilization; negative => backlog pressure (more ready sites than observed weekly delivery capacity). Implementation: for each (m_market, pj_general_contractor) produce two measures: (a) run_rate = COUNT(DISTINCT pj_project_id completed in trailing 12 weeks) / 12 with 0 when none; (b) backlog = COUNT(DISTINCT pj_project_id) meeting readiness gates and not started. gap = run_rate - backlog. Groupable by rgn_region, m_area, m_market, pj_general_contractor.", "parameters": [{"name": "rgn_region", "type": "string", "description": "Filter by rgn region", "required": false, "sample_values": []}, {"name": "m_area", "type": "string", "description": "Filter by m area", "required": false, "sample_values": []}, {"name": "m_market", "type": "string", "description": "Filter by m market", "required": false, "sample_values": []}, {"name": "pj_general_contractor", "type": "string", "description": "Filter by pj general contractor", "required": false, "sample_values": []}, {"name": "pj_program_name", "type": "string", "description": "Filter by pj program name", "required": false, "sample_values": []}, {"name": "pj_project_type", "type": "string", "description": "Filter by pj project type", "required": false, "sample_values": []}], "output_columns": [], "sample_output": [], "row_count": 0}', nl_description: 'For each (rgn_region, m_area, m_market, pj_general_contractor), compute run_rate = distinct projects completed in the last 12 weeks ÷ 12, backlog = distinct projects that are readiness-gated and not started as of CURRENT_DATE, and gap = run_rate − backlog.', node_type: 'CORE', definition: 'For each (rgn_region, m_area, m_market, pj_general_contractor), compute run_rate = distinct projects completed in the last 12 weeks ÷ 12, backlog = distinct projects that are readiness-gated and not started as of CURRENT_DATE, and gap = run_rate − backlog.', kpi_python_function: 'def get_capacity_vs_demand_gap(execute_query, filters=None) -> list[dict]:\n    """Capacity vs Demand Gap per (rgn_region, m_area, m_market, pj_general_contractor).\n\n    run_rate = COUNT(DISTINCT completed projects in trailing 12 weeks) / 12\n    backlog  = COUNT(DISTINCT projects not started as-of CURRENT_DATE that meet readiness gates)\n    gap      = run_rate - backlog\n\n    Notes:\n      - Uses raw SQL against public.stg_ndpd_mbt_tmobile_macro_combined for milestone fields.\n      - Readiness gates are aligned to the Ready Site Backlog KPI\'s 4-gate definition.\n      - Long column names are double-quoted to avoid truncation/case issues.\n    """\n\n    filters = filters or {}\n\n    def esc(v):\n        return str(v).replace("\'", "\'\'")\n\n    where_parts = []\n    if filters.get("rgn_region") is not None:\n        where_parts.append(f"rgn_region = \'{esc(filters[\'rgn_region\'])}\'")\n    if filters.get("m_area") is not None:\n        where_parts.append(f"m_area = \'{esc(filters[\'m_area\'])}\'")\n    if filters.get("m_market") is not None:\n        where_parts.append(f"m_market = \'{esc(filters[\'m_market\'])}\'")\n    if filters.get("pj_general_contractor") is not None:\n        where_parts.append(f"pj_general_contractor = \'{esc(filters[\'pj_general_contractor\'])}\'")\n    if filters.get("pj_program_name") is not None:\n        where_parts.append(f"pj_program_name = \'{esc(filters[\'pj_program_name\'])}\'")\n    if filters.get("pj_project_type") is not None:\n        where_parts.append(f"pj_project_type = \'{esc(filters[\'pj_project_type\'])}\'")\n\n    where_sql = ("WHERE " + " AND ".join(where_parts)) if where_parts else ""\n\n    completed_col = \'"ms_1555_construction_complete_actual"\'\n    started_col = \'"ms_1550_construction_start_actual"\'\n\n    readiness_expr = """\n    (\n      ("ms_1507_tower_ntp_approved_actual" IS NOT NULL\n         OR "pj_a_4100_construction_ntp_accepted_by_gc_finish" IS NOT NULL)\n      AND "pj_a_3925_msI_pickup_date_finish" IS NOT NULL\n      AND "pj_a_4525_power_ready_finish" IS NOT NULL\n      AND ("pj_a_4925_aav_fiber_ready_finish" IS NOT NULL\n         OR "pj_a_4425_mw_installation_complete_finish" IS NOT NULL)\n    )\n    """\n\n    sql = f"""\n    WITH base AS (\n      SELECT\n        rgn_region,\n        m_area,\n        m_market,\n        pj_general_contractor,\n        pj_project_id,\n        {completed_col}::timestamp AS completed_at,\n        {started_col}::timestamp AS started_at,\n        {readiness_expr} AS is_ready\n      FROM public.stg_ndpd_mbt_tmobile_macro_combined\n      {where_sql}\n    ),\n    run_rate_by_grp AS (\n      SELECT\n        rgn_region,\n        m_area,\n        m_market,\n        pj_general_contractor,\n        COUNT(DISTINCT pj_project_id) AS completed_12w\n      FROM base\n      WHERE completed_at IS NOT NULL\n        AND completed_at >= (CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL \'84 days\')\n        AND completed_at < (CURRENT_DATE + INTERVAL \'1 day\')\n      GROUP BY 1,2,3,4\n    ),\n    backlog_by_grp AS (\n      SELECT\n        rgn_region,\n        m_area,\n        m_market,\n        pj_general_contractor,\n        COUNT(DISTINCT pj_project_id) AS ready_not_started\n      FROM base\n      WHERE started_at IS NULL\n        AND is_ready\n      GROUP BY 1,2,3,4\n    ),\n    all_grps AS (\n      SELECT DISTINCT rgn_region, m_area, m_market, pj_general_contractor\n      FROM base\n      WHERE pj_general_contractor IS NOT NULL\n        AND m_market IS NOT NULL\n    )\n    SELECT\n      g.rgn_region,\n      g.m_area,\n      g.m_market,\n      g.pj_general_contractor,\n      COALESCE(r.completed_12w, 0)::numeric / 12.0 AS run_rate,\n      COALESCE(b.ready_not_started, 0) AS backlog,\n      (COALESCE(r.completed_12w, 0)::numeric / 12.0) - COALESCE(b.ready_not_started, 0) AS gap\n    FROM all_grps g\n    LEFT JOIN run_rate_by_grp r\n      ON r.rgn_region = g.rgn_region\n     AND r.m_area = g.m_area\n     AND r.m_market = g.m_market\n     AND r.pj_general_contractor = g.pj_general_contractor\n    LEFT JOIN backlog_by_grp b\n      ON b.rgn_region = g.rgn_region\n     AND b.m_area = g.m_area\n     AND b.m_market = g.m_market\n     AND b.pj_general_contractor = g.pj_general_contractor\n    ORDER BY g.rgn_region, g.m_area, g.m_market, g.pj_general_contractor\n    ;\n    """\n\n    return execute_query(sql)\n', kpi_source_columns: ['rgn_region', 'm_area', 'm_market', 'pj_general_contractor', 'pj_project_id', 'ms_1555_construction_complete_actual', 'ms_1550_construction_start_actual', 'ms_1507_tower_ntp_approved_actual', 'pj_a_4100_construction_ntp_accepted_by_gc_finish', 'pj_a_3925_msI_pickup_date_finish', 'pj_a_4525_power_ready_finish', 'pj_a_4925_aav_fiber_ready_finish', 'pj_a_4425_mw_installation_complete_finish', 'pj_program_name', 'pj_project_type'], session_id: '69a3d22f26e208edc083a06e', label: 'Capacity vs Demand Gap', kpi_related_core_node_ids: ['project', 'market', 'general_contractor'], kpi_relationship_type: 'COMPUTES_FROM', kpi_kpi_id: 'ea9583cb-1701-45ef-a2db-5cc07b01948c', entity_type: 'kpi', kpi_name: 'Capacity vs Demand Gap', name: 'ea9583cb-1701-45ef-a2db-5cc07b01948c', kpi_dimensions: ['rgn_region', 'm_area', 'm_market', 'pj_general_contractor'], kpi_description: 'Measures the execution capacity versus near-term demand by comparing observed weekly delivery capacity to the count of ready-but-not-started sites for each Market and General Contractor, anchored to the current date. Positive values indicate implied spare capacity, while negative values indicate backlog pressure.', status: 'mentioned', node_id: 'ea9583cb-1701-45ef-a2db-5cc07b01948c'});
CREATE (:BKGNode {kpi_source_tables: ['public.stg_ndpd_mbt_tmobile_macro_combined'], nl_business_rule: '', kpi_formula_description: 'For projects with pj_project_status=\'Active\' AND ms_1550_construction_start_actual IS NULL, compute five boolean blockers from milestone NULL checks, then aggregate COUNT(DISTINCT pj_project_id) by (rgn_region, m_area, m_market) [optional + pj_general_contractor] into total_pipeline, fully_ready (0 blockers), each blocked_by_* (blocker true), and blocked_multi (>=2 blockers).', kpi_output_schema: '[{"column": "rgn_region", "type": "string", "description": "Region for aggregation."}, {"column": "m_area", "type": "string", "description": "Area for aggregation."}, {"column": "m_market", "type": "string", "description": "Market for aggregation."}, {"column": "pj_general_contractor", "type": "string", "description": "General contractor (present only when optional grouping by GC is enabled)."}, {"column": "total_pipeline", "type": "int", "description": "Count of distinct active projects that have not started construction."}, {"column": "fully_ready", "type": "int", "description": "Count of distinct projects with none of the five blockers present."}, {"column": "blocked_by_ntp", "type": "int", "description": "Count of distinct projects blocked due to missing NTP approvals/acceptance per definition."}, {"column": "blocked_by_material", "type": "int", "description": "Count of distinct projects blocked due to missing material pickup milestone."}, {"column": "blocked_by_power", "type": "int", "description": "Count of distinct projects blocked due to missing power-ready milestone."}, {"column": "blocked_by_backhaul", "type": "int", "description": "Count of distinct projects blocked due to missing both fiber-ready and MW-install-complete milestones."}, {"column": "blocked_by_access", "type": "int", "description": "Count of distinct projects blocked due to missing pre-construction walk completion milestone."}, {"column": "blocked_multi", "type": "int", "description": "Count of distinct projects with two or more blockers simultaneously."}]', kpi_business_logic: '1) Select population where pj_project_status = \'Active\' AND ms_1550_construction_start_actual IS NULL.\n2) For each distinct pj_project_id, derive blockers:\n   - blocked_ntp = (ms_1507_tower_ntp_approved_actual IS NULL) AND (pj_a_4100_construction_ntp_accepted_by_gc_finish IS NULL)\n   - blocked_material = (pj_a_3925_msI_pickup_date_finish IS NULL)\n   - blocked_power = (pj_a_4525_power_ready_finish IS NULL)\n   - blocked_backhaul = (pj_a_4925_aav_fiber_ready_finish IS NULL) AND (pj_a_4425_mw_installation_complete_finish IS NULL)  # cleared if either is present\n   - blocked_access = (pj_a_3825_pre_construction_walk_complete_finish IS NULL)\n3) Compute blocker_count = number of true blockers among the five.\n4) Group by rgn_region, m_area, m_market (optionally also pj_general_contractor):\n   - total_pipeline = COUNT(DISTINCT pj_project_id)\n   - fully_ready = COUNT(DISTINCT pj_project_id) where blocker_count = 0\n   - blocked_by_ntp/material/power/backhaul/access = COUNT(DISTINCT pj_project_id) where corresponding blocker is true\n   - blocked_multi = COUNT(DISTINCT pj_project_id) where blocker_count >= 2.', kpi_filters: '[{"name": "pj_project_status", "type": "string", "description": "Limits population to active projects (pj_project_status = \'Active\')."}, {"name": "ms_1550_construction_start_actual", "type": "date", "description": "Limits population to projects that have not started construction yet (ms_1550_construction_start_actual IS NULL)."}, {"name": "rgn_region", "type": "string", "description": "Optional filter to restrict results to a specific region."}, {"name": "m_area", "type": "string", "description": "Optional filter to restrict results to a specific area."}, {"name": "m_market", "type": "string", "description": "Optional filter to restrict results to a specific market."}, {"name": "pj_general_contractor", "type": "string", "description": "Optional filter for drill-down to a specific general contractor."}, {"name": "pj_project_id", "type": "string", "description": "Optional filter to restrict results to a specific project."}, {"name": "pj_program_name", "type": "string", "description": "Optional filter to restrict results to a specific program name."}, {"name": "pj_project_type", "type": "string", "description": "Optional filter to restrict results to a specific project type."}, {"name": "group_by_gc", "type": "string", "description": "Optional flag to add pj_general_contractor as a secondary grouping dimension."}]', kpi_contract: '{"function_name": "get_site_blocker_analysis", "node_type": "kpi", "node_id": "df549b33-4d47-4927-9a25-1c9b61911c90", "node_label": "Site Blocker Analysis", "description": "Market-level breakdown of prerequisite blockers for active projects that have not started construction yet. Population: projects where pj_project_status = \'Active\' AND ms_1550_construction_start_actual IS NULL in stg_ndpd_mbt_tmobile_macro_combined. For each project, compute boolean gate blockers: blocked_ntp = (ms_1507_tower_ntp_approved_actual IS NULL AND pj_a_4100_construction_ntp_accepted_by_gc_finish IS NULL); blocked_material = (\\"pj_a_3925_msI_pickup_date_finish\\" IS NULL); blocked_power = (pj_a_4525_power_ready_finish IS NULL); blocked_backhaul = (pj_a_4925_aav_fiber_ready_finish IS NULL AND pj_a_4425_mw_installation_complete_finish IS NULL) meaning either fiber-ready OR MW-complete clears backhaul; blocked_access = (pj_a_3825_pre_construction_walk_complete_finish IS NULL). Aggregate by (rgn_region, m_area, m_market): total_pipeline = COUNT(DISTINCT pj_project_id) over population; fully_ready = count where none of the 5 blockers are true; blocked_by_ntp/material/power/backhaul/access = counts where respective blocker is true; blocked_multi = count where two or more blockers are simultaneously true (sum of boolean flags >= 2). Output is a scorecard table per region/area/market. Optional enhancement: allow filtering or secondary grouping by pj_general_contractor for drill-down, without changing the base market-level KPI.", "parameters": [{"name": "group_by_gc", "type": "string", "description": "Filter by group by gc", "required": false, "sample_values": []}], "output_columns": [{"name": "rgn_region", "type": "string", "nullable": false}, {"name": "m_area", "type": "string", "nullable": false}, {"name": "m_market", "type": "string", "nullable": false}, {"name": "total_pipeline", "type": "number", "nullable": false}, {"name": "fully_ready", "type": "number", "nullable": false}, {"name": "blocked_by_ntp", "type": "number", "nullable": false}, {"name": "blocked_by_material", "type": "number", "nullable": false}, {"name": "blocked_by_power", "type": "number", "nullable": false}, {"name": "blocked_by_backhaul", "type": "number", "nullable": false}, {"name": "blocked_by_access", "type": "number", "nullable": false}, {"name": "blocked_multi", "type": "number", "nullable": false}], "sample_output": [{"rgn_region": "CENTRAL", "m_area": "GREAT LAKES", "m_market": "CHICAGO", "total_pipeline": 2, "fully_ready": 0, "blocked_by_ntp": 1, "blocked_by_material": 1, "blocked_by_power": 1, "blocked_by_backhaul": 2, "blocked_by_access": 0, "blocked_multi": 1}, {"rgn_region": "CENTRAL", "m_area": "GREAT LAKES", "m_market": "CINCINNATI", "total_pipeline": 3, "fully_ready": 0, "blocked_by_ntp": 2, "blocked_by_material": 2, "blocked_by_power": 3, "blocked_by_backhaul": 3, "blocked_by_access": 2, "blocked_multi": 3}, {"rgn_region": "CENTRAL", "m_area": "GREAT LAKES", "m_market": "CLEVELAND", "total_pipeline": 3, "fully_ready": 0, "blocked_by_ntp": 1, "blocked_by_material": 1, "blocked_by_power": 3, "blocked_by_backhaul": 1, "blocked_by_access": 2, "blocked_multi": 2}], "row_count": 10}', nl_description: 'KPI = for projects with pj_project_status=\'Active\' and ms_1550_construction_start_actual IS NULL, compute five boolean blockers (NTP, material, power, backhaul, access) from milestone-null conditions per project, then aggregate distinct pj_project_id counts by (rgn_region, m_area, m_market) [optionally + pj_general_contractor] into total_pipeline, fully_ready (no blockers), each blocked_by_* count, and blocked_multi (>=2 blockers).', node_type: 'CORE', definition: 'KPI = for projects with pj_project_status=\'Active\' and ms_1550_construction_start_actual IS NULL, compute five boolean blockers (NTP, material, power, backhaul, access) from milestone-null conditions per project, then aggregate distinct pj_project_id counts by (rgn_region, m_area, m_market) [optionally + pj_general_contractor] into total_pipeline, fully_ready (no blockers), each blocked_by_* count, and blocked_multi (>=2 blockers).', kpi_python_function: 'def get_site_blocker_analysis(execute_query, filters=None) -> list[dict]:\n    """Market-level breakdown of prerequisite blockers for active projects not started.\n\n    Population:\n      pj_project_status = \'Active\'\n      AND ms_1550_construction_start_actual IS NULL\n\n    Optional enhancement:\n      If filters contains \'group_by_gc\': truthy, include pj_general_contractor in grouping.\n      You can also filter by pj_general_contractor / rgn_region / m_area / m_market via filters.\n    """\n\n    filters = filters or {}\n\n    # Build SQL WHERE clause (PostgreSQL)\n    where_parts = [\n        "pj_project_status = \'Active\'",\n        "ms_1550_construction_start_actual IS NULL"\n    ]\n\n    # Allow common dimension filters (and passthrough of any additional column filters)\n    passthrough_keys = [\n        \'rgn_region\', \'m_area\', \'m_market\',\n        \'pj_general_contractor\', \'pj_project_id\',\n        \'pj_program_name\', \'pj_project_type\'\n    ]\n\n    for k in passthrough_keys:\n        if k in filters and filters.get(k) is not None and filters.get(k) != \'\':\n            v = str(filters.get(k)).replace("\'", "\'\'")\n            where_parts.append(f"{k} = \'{v}\'")\n\n    # NOTE: No date filter is applied because the KPI definition is point-in-time and\n    # milestone fields are nullable timestamps rather than event records.\n\n    where_sql = " AND ".join(where_parts)\n\n    group_by_gc = bool(filters.get(\'group_by_gc\'))\n\n    group_cols = ["rgn_region", "m_area", "m_market"]\n    if group_by_gc:\n        group_cols.append("pj_general_contractor")\n\n    select_group_cols = ",\\n            ".join(group_cols)\n    group_by_sql = ", ".join(group_cols)\n\n    # Raw SQL is required because Tier-1 accessors do not expose the milestone columns needed.\n    sql = f"""\n        SELECT\n            {select_group_cols},\n            pj_project_id,\n            ms_1550_construction_start_actual,\n            ms_1507_tower_ntp_approved_actual,\n            pj_a_4100_construction_ntp_accepted_by_gc_finish,\n            "pj_a_3925_msI_pickup_date_finish",\n            pj_a_4525_power_ready_finish,\n            pj_a_4925_aav_fiber_ready_finish,\n            pj_a_4425_mw_installation_complete_finish,\n            pj_a_3825_pre_construction_walk_complete_finish\n        FROM public.stg_ndpd_mbt_tmobile_macro_combined\n        WHERE {where_sql}\n    """\n\n    rows = execute_query(sql)\n\n    def is_null(x):\n        # Treat None and empty-string as null-like; do NOT treat \'0\' as null.\n        return x is None or (isinstance(x, str) and x.strip() == \'\')\n\n    # Aggregate per group key with DISTINCT project ids\n    agg = {}\n\n    for r in rows:\n        key_vals = []\n        for c in group_cols:\n            key_vals.append(r.get(c))\n        key = tuple(key_vals)\n\n        if key not in agg:\n            agg[key] = {\n                "rgn_region": r.get("rgn_region"),\n                "m_area": r.get("m_area"),\n                "m_market": r.get("m_market"),\n                **({"pj_general_contractor": r.get("pj_general_contractor")} if group_by_gc else {}),\n                "_projects": set(),\n                "total_pipeline": 0,\n                "fully_ready": 0,\n                "blocked_by_ntp": 0,\n                "blocked_by_material": 0,\n                "blocked_by_power": 0,\n                "blocked_by_backhaul": 0,\n                "blocked_by_access": 0,\n                "blocked_multi": 0\n            }\n\n        project_id = r.get("pj_project_id")\n        if project_id in agg[key]["_projects"]:\n            continue\n        agg[key]["_projects"].add(project_id)\n\n        blocked_ntp = is_null(r.get("ms_1507_tower_ntp_approved_actual")) and is_null(r.get("pj_a_4100_construction_ntp_accepted_by_gc_finish"))\n        blocked_material = is_null(r.get("pj_a_3925_msI_pickup_date_finish"))\n        blocked_power = is_null(r.get("pj_a_4525_power_ready_finish"))\n        # Backhaul is cleared if either fiber-ready OR MW-complete is present\n        blocked_backhaul = is_null(r.get("pj_a_4925_aav_fiber_ready_finish")) and is_null(r.get("pj_a_4425_mw_installation_complete_finish"))\n        blocked_access = is_null(r.get("pj_a_3825_pre_construction_walk_complete_finish"))\n\n        blockers = [blocked_ntp, blocked_material, blocked_power, blocked_backhaul, blocked_access]\n        blocker_count = sum(1 for b in blockers if b)\n\n        agg[key]["total_pipeline"] += 1\n        if blocker_count == 0:\n            agg[key]["fully_ready"] += 1\n        if blocked_ntp:\n            agg[key]["blocked_by_ntp"] += 1\n        if blocked_material:\n            agg[key]["blocked_by_material"] += 1\n        if blocked_power:\n            agg[key]["blocked_by_power"] += 1\n        if blocked_backhaul:\n            agg[key]["blocked_by_backhaul"] += 1\n        if blocked_access:\n            agg[key]["blocked_by_access"] += 1\n        if blocker_count >= 2:\n            agg[key]["blocked_multi"] += 1\n\n    # finalize\n    out = []\n    for k, v in agg.items():\n        v.pop("_projects", None)\n        out.append(v)\n\n    # Stable ordering\n    def sort_key(d):\n        base = (\n            str(d.get(\'rgn_region\') or \'\'),\n            str(d.get(\'m_area\') or \'\'),\n            str(d.get(\'m_market\') or \'\')\n        )\n        if group_by_gc:\n            base = base + (str(d.get(\'pj_general_contractor\') or \'\'),)\n        return base\n\n    out.sort(key=sort_key)\n    return out\n', kpi_source_columns: ['pj_project_status', 'ms_1550_construction_start_actual', 'pj_project_id', 'ms_1507_tower_ntp_approved_actual', 'pj_a_4100_construction_ntp_accepted_by_gc_finish', 'pj_a_3925_msI_pickup_date_finish', 'pj_a_4525_power_ready_finish', 'pj_a_4925_aav_fiber_ready_finish', 'pj_a_4425_mw_installation_complete_finish', 'pj_a_3825_pre_construction_walk_complete_finish', 'rgn_region', 'm_area', 'm_market', 'pj_general_contractor', 'pj_program_name', 'pj_project_type'], session_id: '69a3d22f26e208edc083a06e', label: 'Site Blocker Analysis', kpi_related_core_node_ids: ['project', 'market', 'general_contractor'], kpi_relationship_type: 'AGGREGATES', kpi_kpi_id: 'df549b33-4d47-4927-9a25-1c9b61911c90', entity_type: 'kpi', kpi_name: 'Site Blocker Analysis', name: 'df549b33-4d47-4927-9a25-1c9b61911c90', kpi_dimensions: ['rgn_region', 'm_area', 'm_market', 'pj_general_contractor'], kpi_description: 'Market-level breakdown of prerequisite blockers preventing active projects from starting construction. It quantifies how many not-yet-started active projects are ready versus blocked by key prerequisites, supporting prioritization and unblock efforts by market.', status: 'mentioned', node_id: 'df549b33-4d47-4927-9a25-1c9b61911c90'});
CREATE (:BKGNode {kpi_source_tables: ['public.stg_ndpd_mbt_tmobile_macro_combined', 'stg_tmo_copilot_se_rcm'], nl_business_rule: '', kpi_formula_description: 'Per (rgn_region, m_area, m_market) (optionally pj_general_contractor): cycle times = AVG and P50 of non-negative day diffs (ms_1323-ms_1310, ms_1327-ms_1323, ms_1327-ms_1310); backlog = COUNT(DISTINCT pj_project_id) where Active and ms_1310 not null and ms_1327 null; FTR% = 100 * COUNT(completed & rcm_ftr=\'option1\') / COUNT(completed).', kpi_output_schema: '[{"column": "rgn_region", "type": "string", "description": "Region for the scorecard row."}, {"column": "m_area", "type": "string", "description": "Area for the scorecard row."}, {"column": "m_market", "type": "string", "description": "Market for the scorecard row."}, {"column": "pj_general_contractor", "type": "string", "description": "General contractor (included when drilling down by contractor)."}, {"column": "avg_pre_ntp_to_scoping_ready_days", "type": "float", "description": "Average days from ms_1310 to ms_1323 for non-negative differences."}, {"column": "p50_pre_ntp_to_scoping_ready_days", "type": "float", "description": "Median (P50) days from ms_1310 to ms_1323 for non-negative differences."}, {"column": "avg_scoping_ready_to_validated_days", "type": "float", "description": "Average days from ms_1323 to ms_1327 for non-negative differences."}, {"column": "p50_scoping_ready_to_validated_days", "type": "float", "description": "Median (P50) days from ms_1323 to ms_1327 for non-negative differences."}, {"column": "avg_full_scoping_cycle_days", "type": "float", "description": "Average days from ms_1310 to ms_1327 for non-negative differences."}, {"column": "p50_full_scoping_cycle_days", "type": "float", "description": "Median (P50) days from ms_1310 to ms_1327 for non-negative differences."}, {"column": "pending_scoping_count", "type": "int", "description": "Count of distinct active projects with ms_1310 present and ms_1327 missing."}, {"column": "scoping_ftr_pct", "type": "float", "description": "FTR percentage = 100 * (completed with rcm_ftr=\'option1\') / (completed)."}, {"column": "scoping_ftr_numerator_completed_ftr", "type": "int", "description": "Numerator for FTR: count of RCM records with rcm_state=\'completed\' and rcm_ftr=\'option1\'."}, {"column": "scoping_ftr_denominator_completed", "type": "int", "description": "Denominator for FTR: count of RCM records with rcm_state=\'completed\'."}, {"column": "project_count_in_cohort", "type": "int", "description": "Count of distinct projects seen in the macro cohort for the group."}]', kpi_business_logic: '1) From stg_ndpd_mbt_tmobile_macro_combined, group projects by (rgn_region, m_area, m_market) (optionally include pj_general_contractor) using pj_project_id as grain.\n2) Pre-NTP to Scoping Ready: for projects with ms_1310 and ms_1323 present and (ms_1323 - ms_1310) >= 0, compute AVG and P50 of the day difference.\n3) Scoping Ready to Validated: for projects with ms_1323 and ms_1327 present and (ms_1327 - ms_1323) >= 0, compute AVG and P50 of the day difference.\n4) Full Scoping Cycle: for projects with ms_1310 and ms_1327 present and (ms_1327 - ms_1310) >= 0, compute AVG and P50 of the day difference.\n5) Pending Scoping Count: count distinct pj_project_id where pj_project_status=\'Active\' AND ms_1310 is not null AND ms_1327 is null.\n6) From stg_tmo_copilot_se_rcm, compute FTR% where denominator is count of records with rcm_state=\'completed\' and numerator is count of records with rcm_state=\'completed\' AND rcm_ftr=\'option1\'.\n7) Attach FTR to the same group either by joining rcm_site_id to s_site_id from the macro table to inherit (rgn_region, m_area, m_market), or (if join is unreliable) compute FTR grouped by (rcm_region, rcm_market) and present alongside macro-based results.', kpi_filters: '[{"name": "rgn_region", "type": "string", "description": "Limits results to a specific region."}, {"name": "m_area", "type": "string", "description": "Limits 