date - ms_1323::date`.\\n- Full Scoping Cycle (days): where `ms_1310...` and `ms_1327...` not null and diff>=0, compute AVG and P50 of `ms_1327::date - ms_1310::date`.\\n- Pending Scoping Count: `pending_scoping_count = COUNT(DISTINCT pj_project_id)` for projects with `pj_project_status=\'Active\' AND ms_1310_pre_construction_package_received_actual IS NOT NULL AND ms_1327_scoping_and_quoting_package_validated_actual IS NULL`.\\n\\nFTR component (secondary source): use `stg_tmo_copilot_se_rcm` and compute scoping FTR% as `100 * numerator/denominator` where `denominator = COUNT(*) FILTER (WHERE rcm_state=\'completed\')` and `numerator = COUNT(*) FILTER (WHERE rcm_state=\'completed\' AND rcm_ftr=\'option1\')`. Prefer to join into the same output by mapping RCM records to markets/regions (join option A: `rcm_site_id = s_site_id` from macro table to inherit `(rgn_region,m_area,m_market)`; option B: if join is unreliable, compute FTR grouped by `(rcm_region, rcm_market)` and present alongside macro-based market results). Optionally support drill-down by `rcm_assignee` for scoping engineer performance.\\n\\nEntities involved: Project/Site (macro combined table) + Scoping Package (RCM tracker). Output is a per-market scorecard with multiple measures: cycle-time averages/medians, pending scoping count, and FTR%.", "parameters": [{"name": "start_date", "type": "date", "description": "Filter by start date", "required": false, "sample_values": []}, {"name": "end_date", "type": "date", "description": "Filter by end date", "required": false, "sample_values": []}, {"name": "rgn_region", "type": "string", "description": "Filter by rgn region", "required": false, "sample_values": []}, {"name": "m_area", "type": "string", "description": "Filter by m area", "required": false, "sample_values": []}, {"name": "m_market", "type": "string", "description": "Filter by m market", "required": false, "sample_values": []}, {"name": "pj_general_contractor", "type": "string", "description": "Filt